This is the Tanglu Website source, powered by Django.

Django version: 1.5

----------------
Packages Needed:
----------------
See file REQUIREMENTS


----------------
Installation:
----------------
Use virtualenv to install required packages and avoid modifying your system
packages.

* Create virtual environment:
    $ virtualenv --no-site-packages ENV

* Activate virtual environment:
    $ source ENV/bin/activate

* Edit REQUIREMENTS to use MySQL or PostGreSQL

* Install required packages:
    $ pip install -r REQUIREMENTS


----------------
Configuration:
----------------
Edit database informations in tanglu/settings.py file and run these commands:
    $ python manage.py syncdb --all
    $ python manage.py migrate --fake

These commands are from the South package and they should be run as above
everytime a database modification is required.
See more at http://south.readthedocs.org/en/latest/tutorial/part1.html

* First database sync
If it is the first time the database is synched, a administrator account
creation will be requested. Just choose 'yes', to create one, and enter the
required informations.

Now, run the server.
